	msged-te-05): Fixed the time slicing code for the DOS and DPMI
	versions.

1998-08-19 Wednesday 23:26  tobi

	* config.c (1.4): - Added the "Colors" and the "Shadows" switch.

1998-08-19 Wednesday 23:25  tobi

	* ansi.c (1.4): - Added support for Linux function keys - Added
	support for Double ESC (pressing two times ESC in short sequence  
	is interpreted as a single ESC) - Added support for
	"monochromifying" the output in order to support   terminals that
	do not understand ANSI color codes like Linux xterm   or AIX xterm.

1998-08-17 Monday 09:46  tobi

	* msghelp.src (1.2), doc/whatsnew.txt (1.6), doc/manual/makefile
	(1.3), doc/manual/msged.texi (1.6): Updated online help, docs and
	whatsnew files.

1998-08-17 Monday 09:45  tobi

	* msg.c (1.5): Made the MSGED Squish interface layer independent of
	little/big endian and structure packing issues.

1998-08-17 Monday 09:43  tobi

	* makefile.djg (1.2): Fix: Executable is stripped now (it gets
	smaller)

1998-08-17 Monday 09:38  tobi

	* list.c (1.3, msged-te-05-second-try), maintmsg.c (1.3),
	maintmsg.h (1.2, msged-te-05-second-try) (utags: msged-te-05): -
	Added new keys + and - in list screen to allow marking/demarking of
	ALL   messages in that area - Fixed Alt+M in message list screen so
	that it moves all marked messages,   but only asks once where to
	move them. (Same for copying, forwarding,   redirecting, and
	deleting).  - Added a progress info window with the possibility to
	interrupt the	process for copying, forwarding, redirecting and
	deleting a set of marked   messages in message list screen.

1998-08-17 Monday 09:36  tobi

	* help.c (1.2): Fix for Borland C / DOS

1998-08-17 Monday 09:34  tobi

	* dirute.h (1.2), fecfg145.h (1.2) (utags: msged-te-05-second-try,
	msged-te-05): Fix for DJGPP

1998-08-17 Monday 09:33  tobi

	* charset.c (1.3), charset.h (1.2, msged-te-05-second-try,
	msged-te-05): Change: On UNIX, the character set translation files
	are expected to be named ~/.msged.readmaps and ~/.msged.writmaps
	instead of READMAPS.DAT and WRITMAPS.DAT from now on.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:42  tobi

	* makefile.bcd (1.2, msged-te-05-second-try, msged-te-05),
	makefile.bsd (1.5, msged-te-05-second-try, msged-te-05),
	makefile.rxw (1.2), makefile.unx (1.3, msged-te-05-second-try,
	msged-te-05): Updated makefiles: Removed the NO_SQUISH_LOCKING
	compiler switch.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:39  tobi

	* doc/: whatsnew.txt (1.5), manual/msged.texi (1.5): Updated docs.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:37  tobi

	* readmail.c (1.4): Fixes for character translation and SOT/EOT
	handling.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:37  tobi

	* textfile.c (1.2): Added support for shell expansion of ~ to home
	directory when importing/exporting text.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:35  tobi

	* msged.h (1.2): Added variable definitions: ST->input_charset and
	SQ->squish_lock

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:35  tobi

	* msg.c (1.4): Added support for the SquishLock switch, remove the
	NO_SQUISH_LOCKING compile-time switch.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:34  tobi

	* memextra.c (1.2): xstrdup no longer crashes when passed a NULL
	pointer.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:33  tobi

	* init.c (1.2): Added initialisations.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:33  tobi

	* environ.c (1.2): Environment variables with underscore in them
	are now supported.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:32  tobi

	* config.h (1.2, msged-te-05-second-try, msged-te-05): Added
	prototype for shell_expand

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:32  tobi

	* config.c (1.3): - Added support for shell-expansion of ~ for home
	directories.  - Added new keyword AssumeCharset and the SquishLock
	switch.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:31  tobi

	* charset.c (1.2): Fixed a bug when writing in IBMPC charset on a
	LATIN-1 system.

1998-07-28 Tuesday 15:30  tobi

	* ansi.c (1.3): Added ANSI codes for function keys and some fixes
	for the AIX console.

1998-07-25 Saturday 02:11  tobi

	* makefile.lnx (1.4): Don't use curses for Linux.

1998-07-25 Saturday 02:10  tobi

	* doc/manual/msged.texi (1.4): Added chapter about CHRS kludge.

1998-07-25 Saturday 02:09  tobi

	* msg.c (1.3): Fix: Return code of MsgLock was not evaluated.

1998-07-25 Saturday 02:09  tobi

	* makefile.ibo (1.1, msged-te-05-second-try, msged-te-05): Added
	makefile for IBM CSet

1998-07-25 Saturday 02:09  tobi

	* config.c (1.2): It is now possible to use more then one
	AreafileFlags keyword.

